    <text type="letter">
        <body>
            <opener>  
                <dateline>
                    <name type="place">Camden New Jersey</name>
                    <date when="1882-04-12">April 12 '82</date>
                </dateline>
                <salute>Dear Sirs</salute>
            </opener>
            <p>Yours of 10th just <choice><abbr>rec'd</abbr><expan>received</expan></choice><ptr target="upa.00207_n1"/>&#8212;If you desire to cease to
                be the publishers of <hi rend="italic">Leaves of Grass</hi> unless I make the
                excisions required by the District Attorney&#8212;if this is your settled
                decision&#8212;I see indeed no other way than "some reasonable arrangement for
                turning the plates over" to me&#8212;What is the <choice>
                    <abbr>am't</abbr>
                    <expan>amount</expan>
                </choice> of royalty due me, according
                to contract, from the sales altogether? &#38; what is your valuation of the
                plates?</p>
            <closer>
                <signed>Walt Whitman</signed>
            </closer>
        </body>
    </text>
